{
    "text": "Setting up your future self for success",
    "created": "Mon, 12 Sep 2022 11:45:19 GMT",
    "type": "outline",
    "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/09/12/114519.html?title=settingUpYourFutureSelfForSuccess",
    "subs": [
        {
            "text": "Sascha <a href=\"https://zettelkasten.de/posts/how-to-create-value-in-zettelkasten/\">sets out a progression</a> of increasingly meaningful encounters with a piece of reading. Reading itself, then >> collecting quotations >> creating excerpts >> composing \"<a href=\"https://zettelkasten.de/posts/create-zettel-from-reading-notes/\">atomic notes</a>\" that distill the reading usefully >> create connections and even tools among and with some of these elements.",
            "created": "Mon, 12 Sep 2022 11:45:29 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/09/12/114519.html?title=settingUpYourFutureSelfForSuccess#a114529"
        },
        {
            "text": "Interestingly, Sascha points out that the further down this path a reader goes, the more valuable the results are for that reader in the future because present-self has more richly prepared the soil for some future effort or investigation. (<a href=\"https://andysylvester.com/2022/09/07/some-thoughts-on-why-write/\">Via Andy S.</a>)",
            "created": "Mon, 12 Sep 2022 11:46:29 GMT",
            "permalink": "http://oldschool.scripting.com/KenSmith/2022/09/12/114519.html?title=settingUpYourFutureSelfForSuccess#a114629"
        }
    ]
}

{
