{
    "text": "In the final ten minutes of the documentary, as the campaign for president was collapsing, the filmmaker caught the candidate in a quiet room and asked for some reflections. What does it feel like to you now as the campaign is collapsing? All those people at the different stops telling you their stories, asking for your help, and you're not going to be able to provide it--what does that feel like? It was a stupid question. Better would be: All these people were telling you their stories about what they and other people like them need or hope for--what have these stories taught you about the country and the work we have cut out for us going forward? Running for public office is only a journey of personal emotion for the candidate. For the rest of us, it's part of the work of getting things more right in the country. Focus, focus . . .",
    "created": "Mon, 12 Sep 2022 11:58:29 GMT",
